parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while in motion, leading to a loss of power steering and braking, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ignition switch only goes to ACC mode and will not turn to the off position
the key gets stuck in the ignition
the vehicle quits running while driving
and the vehicle loses power steering and braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down while in motion, leading to a loss of power steering and braking, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle quits running while driving
and the vehicle loses power steering and braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause difficulties in filling the gas tank, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The gas tank is not working right
it's difficult to fill the gas tank
and the gas pump pops out and doesn't let the driver put gas in the tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel can cause inaccurate readings, leading to confusion and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The instrument panel provides inaccurate readings for various components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speed control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's speed increases slowly while driving
requiring the driver to brake to maintain a safe speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal travels to the floorboard
grinding or crunching noise when braking
pulsing or abnormal operation of the ABS system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: grinding or crunching noise when braking
pulsing or abnormal operation of the ABS system

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake components can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pads and rotors worn out prematurely
brake calipers and shoes needing replacement
squealing or crunching noise when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the vehicle's brake system to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.
The failure of brake lines due to rust can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Filler Neck Separation and Fuel Line Fracture
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank filler neck separation and fuel line fracture can cause fuel to leak onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and potential accident risk.
symptoms: fuel dripping from the fuel tank inlet check valve
fuel leaking from the seam of the fuel tank
fuel pressure regulator dripping fuel onto the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Ignition system malfunction can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Premature failure of the front wheel bearings can cause loud grinding or growling noises, vibrations, and potentially lead to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: and humming sounds coming from the front wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Overheating and Head Gasket Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to the engine, leading to costly repairs, and potentially resulting in a blown head gasket, which can cause the engine to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine temperature gauge rises to the red zone

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: the lights on the radio intermittently illuminate
the vehicle loses steering and brakes
